An 'angel shark' is a shark in the genus 'Squatina', which are unusual in having
flattened bodies and broad pectoral fins that give them a strong resemblance to
rays. Twenty-three species are known to exist in the genus, which is the only
one in its family, 'Squatinidae', and order 'Squatiniformes'. They occur
worldwide in temperate and tropical seas. Most species inhabit shallow temperate
or tropical seas, but one species inhabits deeper water, down to .<ref
name=EoF/>
